  "claim_boundary": "places persistent observer-facing record objects into the observer-derived modular-response H3 chart using only sampled observers that see the object. A chart receipt reports whole-object-set compactness against shuffled observer-object incidence. A populated-bulk receipt is narrower: it requires either a localized non-boundary object subpopulation that beats the same localized non-boundary criterion under shuffled H3 observer incidence, or a robust whole-population compactness-distribution separation with the non-boundary leakage audit passing, plus the strict modular-response H3 chart gate. The localized-object precursor can pass on the intermediate control-separation H3 receipt, but the populated-bulk receipt cannot. This is not a CMB or particle claim. When split_h3_components is true, broad observer-visible packet classes are split into local H3 components and the same split memberships are held fixed under shuffled-H3 controls, preventing the control from choosing new local components after observer H3 labels are randomized.",
